characters.name: ALAN GRANT
characters.description: Dr. Alan Grant is a rugged, no-nonsense palaeontologist with a deep passion for dinosaurs. He's dedicated to his fieldwork, preferring the company of fossils over people, especially children. Grant initially resists modern technology and is sceptical of flashy scientific showmanship. However, his intellect and bravery are evident as he adapts quickly to the dangers of Jurassic Park. Throughout the story, his character arc evolves from a solitary scientist into a protective, resourceful guardian, particularly toward Lex and Tim. Grant's knowledge, pragmatism, and resilience are key to surviving the chaos unleashed by resurrected dinosaurs.

characters.name: ELLIE SATTLER
characters.description: Dr. Ellie Sattler is a bright, quick-witted palaeobotanist with a sharp mind and adventurous spirit. She's passionate about science and equally unafraid to get her hands dirty in the field. Ellie is both intuitive and analytical, often recognising issues before others, particularly related to the unnatural environment of the park. Her compassion and assertiveness make her a stabilising force amid chaos. Throughout the story, she proves herself courageous and capable‚Äîrescuing others, challenging authority, and confronting danger head-on. Ellie's empathy, intelligence, and strength position her as a pivotal figure in both the park‚Äôs operation and its ultimate unravelling.

characters.name: IAN MALCOLM
characters.description: Dr. Ian Malcolm is a charismatic, eccentric mathematician specialising in chaos theory. With his sardonic wit, black wardrobe, and philosophical musings, he brings both comic relief and critical insight into the story. Malcolm warns of the inherent unpredictability in Jurassic Park's genetic experimentation, famously stating, "Life finds a way." Though skeptical and cynical, he's not without courage‚Äîplacing himself in harm‚Äôs way to protect others. His injury limits his mobility, but not his sharp commentary. Malcolm‚Äôs intellectual depth and iconoclastic worldview serve as a moral compass, emphasising the folly of controlling nature with technology.

characters.name: JOHN HAMMOND
characters.description: John Hammond is the visionary billionaire behind Jurassic Park. Enthusiastic, charming, and stubbornly optimistic, he envisions a theme park that will amaze the world by bringing dinosaurs back to life. Though well-intentioned, his blind faith in science and control systems proves dangerously na√Øve. Hammond is more of a showman than a scientist, often glossing over ethical and safety concerns. As the park unravels, he begins to confront the consequences of his ambition. His arc is a tragic one‚Äîmoving from awe-inspired creator to a man humbled by nature‚Äôs unpredictability and the limits of human control.

characters.name: TIM MURPHY
characters.description: Tim Murphy is John Hammond‚Äôs curious and intelligent grandson. A dinosaur enthusiast, he idolises Dr. Grant and quickly bonds with him. Tim's youthful enthusiasm and knowledge prove useful, especially when he recognises dinosaur species and scientific details. Despite his age, Tim shows remarkable bravery and resilience, surviving a T-Rex attack and even helping reboot the park‚Äôs computer systems. He‚Äôs resourceful, clever, and emotionally strong under pressure. His relationship with Grant softens the latter‚Äôs stance on children, forming one of the film‚Äôs more touching subplots. Tim represents the awe and wonder that Jurassic Park was intended to inspire.

characters.name: LEX MURPHY
characters.description: Lex Murphy is Tim‚Äôs older sister, a tech-savvy and quick-witted teen who initially seems out of her depth. She‚Äôs less enthusiastic about dinosaurs than Tim, but her computer skills become critical when the group must restore the park‚Äôs security systems. Lex matures quickly under pressure, showing moments of great courage, especially in protecting her younger brother. Her character breaks the stereotype of the helpless child, proving integral to the group's survival. She also plays a key emotional role, reinforcing the theme of family and resilience. Lex balances her fears with quick thinking and emotional strength.
